  "text": "As substitution model, we assume the standard F81 stochastic model of nucleotide substitution [CITATION_1] . The algorithm computes the optimal maximum likelihood sequence alignment using three matrices, one for each evolutionary event (i.e., substitution, deletion, and insertion). The algorithm is given by the following dynamic programming recurrence:",
